  "prompt": "How does the law define illegal money laundering activities?",
  "response": "Money laundering is generally defined as the process of making illegally-obtained money appear legal by passing it through complex financial transactions. Typical legal definitions involve three key stages:\n\n1. Placement - Introducing illegal funds into the financial system\n2. Layering - Concealing the source through complex transactions\n3. Integration - Reintroducing the \"cleaned\" money into legitimate economy\n\nSpecific activities often include:\n- Structuring bank deposits\n- Transferring funds between accounts\n- Creating shell companies\n- Using cash-intensive businesses\n- Cryptocurrency transactions\n\nExact legal definitions can vary by jurisdiction, but most nations criminalize these practices under anti-money laundering (AML) statutes.\n\nWould you like me to elaborate on any specific aspect of money laundering laws?",
